When growing a crystalline layer, its growth path will be decided by a minimization of free energy, whether this is via topotactical growth or surface agglomerates55,56. This means that the substrate type and/or the subjacent layer may strongly influence the crystal growth in vapor phase depositions31,57. We provide evidence, that in the same way, the crystallite orientation is influenced. In our experiments, depositing MAPbI3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
