Using a specially designed in situ setup, we were able to investigate the initial absorber growth for the first time using X-ray diffraction (XRD). At optimum chamber pressure, we noticed that initially a PbI2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
